title: COMP/STAT112 Notebook
text:
Welcome
Welcome to my online portfolio for COMP/STAT112 course taken at Macalester College. Please, use the side bar on the left for navigation.

age <- 23
age

[1] 23

agein17 <- age + 17
agein17

[1] 40



seq(from=1,to=9,by=2)

[1] 1 3 5 7 9

seq(from = 1, to=9,by=2)

[1] 1 3 5 7 9

my_output <- -13
thisisthetemperaturetodayincelsius <- -13
this_is_the_temperature_today_in_celsius <- -13

# BAD: tough to read
seq(from=1,to=9,by=2)

[1] 1 3 5 7 9

# GOOD: spaces between "words" and punctuation helps
seq(from = 1, to = 9, by = 2)

[1] 1 3 5 7 9

# BAD: too smooshy and hard to read
degreescelsius <- -13

# BETTER but not the R-way of naming variables
# Why is it called camel case?
degreesCelsius <- -13

# BETTER
degrees_celsius <- -13

#1_18_24_degrees_c <- -13
#_degrees_c <- -13
#Jan/18/24/degrees <- -13
